articles.title: Mosquito-transmitted dengue fever may provide immunity against COVID-19: Study - DNA India
articles.description: A new study that analyzed the coronavirus outbreak in Brazil has found a link between the spread of the virus and past outbreaks of dengue fever that suggests exposure to the mosquito-transmitted illness may provide some level of immunity against COVID-19.
